headline: Are Kroger Shares Still a Bargain After 20% Gain and New Tech Partnerships?
summary: If you’re eyeing Kroger’s stock and wondering if it’s a buy, hold, or time to take profits, you’re not the only one. Over the last five years, investors have seen a remarkable 132.9% return, and even over just the past year, shares have tacked on nearly 20%. Sure, the last week showed a modest dip of 3%, but it’s the kind of short-term movement that savvy investors have learned to put in context, especially after a solid 2.5% climb over the last month and an 8.3% gain year-to-date.
